            <p class="pb-4 m-0">Let’s discuss them. </p>
            <h3>1.  Ebook Pricing </h3>
            <p class="pb-4 m-0">Amazon allows total control over the eBook pricing, which in turn impacts the royalties that are earned. As discussed, individuals can either choose 35% or 70%, but the latter has some specifications, such as setting the list price within a certain range.</p>
            <h3>2.  Paperback Pricing</h3>
            <p class="pb-4 m-0">
                The paperback pricing also impacts the overall costs of <a href="self-publishing-service">self publishing on Amazon</a> as interested individuals decide the list price, and then the platform will make deductions based on the printing and royalties.
The printing cost depends on several factors, such as the total number of pages of the book, ink type, trim size, etc.
            <h3>3. Royalty Rates</h3>
                The royalty rate that you opt for will impact the amount you earn for every sale. A higher royalty rate has a couple of requirements that you need to keep in mind when self publishing your book. These requirements include pricing criteria or distribution limitations.
            <h3>4. Printing and Distribution Costs</h3>
                When using Kindle Direct Publishing Print, your books will be printed when someone places an order. Put simply, KDP Print utilizes print-on-demand technology. So, the printing costs will be subtracted from the list price, including the royalties. Distribution costs may also add to the expenses if you decide to go for an expanded distribution of paperbacks.
